Reminder that, after all, life is good. The world is filled with beauty.

With years, plastics will rot, evil men will burn, every wound will heal, every happy moment will return, all seeds will grow, all love shall blossom forever.

So is written in the roots and it the clouds.

We often quote parts of the Bible about demons, about suffering, but it is all said by Christ Himself:

Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness: for they shall be filled.

In the end, it all shall be well. Better than you can imagine. ALL. SHALL. BE. WELL.
